Added Claude headless execution to the parallel runner while keeping Codex as the default. The main changes are in [runner/parallel-codex-runner.py](/C:/Users/ColsonR/Agent/runner/parallel-codex-runner.py#L29) and [runner/claude-headless.sh](/C:/Users/ColsonR/Agent/runner/claude-headless.sh#L1).

- [runner/parallel-codex-runner.py](/C:/Users/ColsonR/Agent/runner/parallel-codex-runner.py#L1414) now accepts `--executor {codex,claude}` and `--claude-bin`, with Codex still the default.
- [runner/parallel-codex-runner.py](/C:/Users/ColsonR/Agent/runner/parallel-codex-runner.py#L766) builds a Claude-specific prompt that carries the owned-path constraints and keeps commits in the runner, so the existing verify/ownership/commit flow is preserved.
- [runner/parallel-codex-runner.py](/C:/Users/ColsonR/Agent/runner/parallel-codex-runner.py#L798) adds a Windows Claude path that prefers the new Bash wrapper for default `claude`, unsets `CLAUDECODE`, and falls back to direct CLI execution for non-Windows or custom `--claude-bin`.
- [runner/claude-headless.sh](/C:/Users/ColsonR/Agent/runner/claude-headless.sh#L1) runs `claude -p` from a prompt file instead of passing the full prompt as a raw argument, which avoids the quoting/length problems that were blocking Windows usage.

Verified:
- `python -m py_compile runner/parallel-codex-runner.py`
- `python runner/parallel-codex-runner.py --help`
- `python runner/parallel-codex-runner.py --manifest dispatch/parallel-batch.manifest.json --validate-only`
- `python runner/parallel-codex-runner.py --manifest dispatch/parallel-batch.manifest.json --executor claude --dry-run --no-cc-merge`

